channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Health Officials Urge Doctors to Address IUD Insertion Pain
item.description: As videos describing the procedure as agonizing spread on social media, new guidelines advise physicians to consider various anesthetics.

item.title: Middle East Crisis: Arab States Urge Iran to Show Restraint in Conflict With Israel
item.description: Several countries in the Middle East, led by U.S. allies, are encouraging Iran to craft a limited response to the killing of a Hamas leader in Tehran that would avoid a wider regional war.

item.title: Yes, social workers can earn six-figures. Here are the top-paying companies right now
item.description: Social work isn’t traditionally associated with high-paying careers, but rising demand has led to some relatively high-paying social worker jobs.

item.title: Trump Dangles New Tax Cut Proposals With Real Political Appeal
item.description: The most recent and costliest of Mr. Trump’s ideas would end income taxes on Social Security benefits.

item.title: As Iran Braces for War, Its Citizens are Kept in the Dark
item.description: Iranians say they have not been told how to prepare should broad hostilities break out between their country and Israel.

item.title: Tim Walz and JD Vance agree on something: Diet Mountain Dew. But is the non-partisan pop healthy?
item.description: The chartreuse soda contains three artificial sweeteners and various additives. How safe are they?

item.title: 30 Months After Their Games Ended, U.S. Figure Skaters Get Golds
item.description: In a ceremony in Paris, the American team received the medals they won after the Russian team, featuring Kamila Valieva, was disqualified.

item.title: Exclusive: Crypto vet Meltem Demirors raising $75 million for two venture funds under Crucible Capital
item.description: Demirors has carved out a prominent voice in the digital assets sector through her angel investing and vocal Twitter presence.

item.title: Connie Chiume, 72, Dies; ‘Black Panther’ Actor Bridged S. Africa Eras
item.description: Her career began during apartheid and outlived it, reaching a personal milestone in a blockbuster movie and its sequel.

item.title: As Biden’s Presidency Wanes, U.S. and Asian Nations Do a Delicate Dance
item.description: On an epic trip, Secretary of State Antony J. Blinken tried to reassure Asian leaders about American commitments. But China remains the enduring backyard behemoth.
